Programme & Project Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Local (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Personnel Area: Corporate Services 

Branch: Information services 

Salary Range: BAND 8 $150,432 to $162,791 + Superannuation 

Work type: Temporary Full-time 

Location: Brisbane Square 

Duration: Aug 2026

Are you a business analysis guru with a passion for public service? Do you thrive on setting standards, leading talented people and turning complex problems into community-focused solutions? If so, we want you to lead our ICT Business Analyst Practice!

The Information Services branch (ISB) at Brisbane City Council is looking for a Business Analyst Practice Manager. You’ll be the driving force behind business analysis excellence across the ISB Program of Work. You’ll lead a team of brilliant Business Analysts, set the gold standard for analysis practices and provide business analysis across a diverse portfolio of Council ICT projects.

 A Day in the Life

You might start your morning with a stand-up meeting about digitising permit applications, or debriefing with your team around artificial intelligence, then spend your afternoon running an elicitation workshop with stakeholders relating to cyber security, and end the day celebrating a team win with coffee and cake. No two days are the same—and that’s just how we like it. Our portfolio is extensive, which means you and your team could be working on a variety of exciting projects, making a real difference for our people and the residents of Brisbane.  

Our Business 

Brisbane City Council is Australia’s largest local government, with more than 9,000 employees, an annual budget of almost $4 billion and assets in excess of $34 billion. As an organisation we are dedicated to ensuring the Brisbane of tomorrow becomes even better than the Brisbane of today. We nurture innovation, value sustainability, and support strong economic growth. 

Our Branch 

Information Services branch (ISB) supports and enables nearly all of Council’s day-to-day activities and services through efficient, flexible and innovative ICT solutions. We lead the ICT strategy that supports the business objectives of Council as a whole, as well as information management and ICT service delivery in Council. 

What You’ll Do

Champion customer-focused innovation and knowledge sharing
Lead with values and performance excellence, in line with Council’s Leadership Blueprint
Create, champion, drive and support standards of business analysis across ISB
Develop strategic business analysis and monitoring strategies, systems and processes enabling consistent and optimal service delivery in line with strategic objectives
Design monitoring strategies and systems for consistent service delivery
Oversee the design and delivery of dashboards and reports to track benefits
Advocate for transparent governance and end-to-end process excellence

What You Bring

Proven leadership in business analysis and practice development
Sharp analytical skills and a strategic mindset
A collaborative spirit, excellent communication skills and stakeholder engagement abilities
A passion for public service and a commitment to making a difference in the community through technology
Exceptional leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills

Why join us

Community Impact: Join Australia’s largest local government and make a real difference, delivering projects that directly benefit the community and contribute to the shaping of Brisbane's future.  

Work-Life balance: Enjoy flexible work arrangements, personal and professional development opportunities and generous leave provisions.  

Dynamic work environment:  Work in a collaborative, future-focused team that values innovation, inclusion, and excellence 

Employee Benefits: Access employee benefits that matter to you - including generous superannuation, free gym membership, access to volunteer leave and many more.  

Benefits of working for Council: CLICK HERE 

Ready to lead with purpose and personality? Apply now and help us build a smarter, more connected, more sustainable Brisbane—one project at a time. 

How to apply:  Click on the 'Apply' button below to complete your online application. Please upload your current resume and cover letter (of no more than one page) that demonstrates how you meet the requirements of this role. 

Please note: Eligibility for internal only roles includes external applicants who identify as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander and/or as a person living with a disability. Applicants from these groups are required to complete the diversity and inclusion questions on the application form to enable Council to determine eligibility.

This role requires a Criminal History Check.

For more information:  Please contact John Hefez on 3178 3859 or john.hefez@brisbane.qld.gov.au

People from diverse backgrounds, including those living with a disability and/or Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, who may have questions about the recruitment process or working at Council, are encouraged to reach out to the contact above, who can connect you with a member of Council’s Diversity and Inclusion team.

Application Closing Date: Monday 13th October 2025 at 11:55pm AEST

Brisbane City Council is a multi-award winning accessible and inclusive workplace where our people represent the diverse communities we serve, are supported, and can feel safe. Council has been awarded Employer of the Year at the National Disability Awards and has been recognised multiple times with ‘Gold Employer’ status from the Australian Workplace Equality Index for LGBTI inclusion.

Ad Text:
Campus Location: North Sydney, Australia | Brisbane, Australia

Job No: APTAV119480#001

Data Analyst - Join Our Impactful Team!

Make your mark in a role where your insights drive real change and innovation across our workforce systems

Thrive in a collaborative, purpose-driven team that values growth, inclusion, and innovation

ACU offers 17% employer superannuation, salary packaging and generous leave provisions

Full time, continuing role at our North Sydney or Brisbane campus with some hybrid flexibility

About the role:

Operating within HRIS Strategy and Reporting, the Workforce Reporting Data Analyst provides targeted analytical support to enhance evidence-based decision-making across ACU's workforce and people management processes. This involves integrating and interpreting data related to individuals, positions, organisational structures, workloads, and process outcomes. Additonally, the role also contextualises internal data against sector-wide benchmarks to inform strategic workforce planning, policy development, and organisational change initiatives.

For full position details, refer to the position description.

Contact:

General enquiries can be sent to Richard Lewis, National Manager Workforce Systems Strategy and Reporting at: Richard.Lewis@acu.edu.au

What we offer:

The University pursues an excellence agenda and offers an environment where staff are welcomed and safe, and valued through development, participation and involvement.

Total remuneration valued to $138,111 - $154,383 total rem (pro rata) pa, including salary component $116,706 - $130,478 (pro rata) pa (HEW 8), employer contribution to superannuation and annual leave loading.

17% employer superannuation contributions to eligible continuing and fixed-term staff.

Annual leave loading of an equivalent to 17.5% of four weeks' salary pro rata payable, dependent on your commencement date.

As an ACU staff member, you will have access to generous benefits which include but not limited to: flexible work, study leave, a variety of leave provisions and salary packaging. Find out more information about the benefits or working at ACU here.

How to Apply:

Step 1: Review the Position Description and become familiar with Our Mission and the Application process

Step 2: Click the 'View Position Description and Apply' button, and populate your candidate application details, including your:

resume (maximum 5 pages).

responses to the Selection Criteria and Core Competencies in a cover letter (maximum 2 pages) or in the online Declaration and Criteria application page.

brief online responses to any pre-screening employment questions.

Applications close: 13-OCT-2025 at 11:59pm AUS Eastern Standard Time

Candidates must hold Australian work rights to apply for this position. For permanent/ continuing roles, applicants must have permanent work rights. For further information visit Immigration and Citizenship(homeaffairs.gov.au)

Your Privacy of personal information is maintained in accordance with ACU policy. For more details visit: www.acu.edu.au/careers

ACU is committed to fostering an inclusive workplace culture that values diversity and enables our people to reach their potential. This is underpinned by our mission and values, grounded in our respect for all people and the advancement of the common good. In line with our commitment to equity, diversity and inclusion we welcome candidates from all backgrounds and lived experiences. ACU is recognised as a Veteran Employment Supporter and veterans are encouraged to apply. ACU offers support for candidates that may require adjustments through the recruitment process. Please contact recruitment@acu.edu.au to discuss your requirements in confidence.

About ACU:

Australian Catholic University (ACU) is an inclusive community which welcomes students and staff of all beliefs. ACU has over 2,500 staff supporting more than 34,000 students across eight campuses - Ballarat, Brisbane, Canberra, Melbourne, North Sydney, Strathfield, Blacktown and Rome.

ACU aspires to be a home for our staff, offer the care of a family and develop an academic and professional community. Whatever your faith or culture, and whether you are academic or professional staff, there are many opportunities both for learning and contributing at ACU.

As valued members of our community, all staff members are expected to have an understanding of ACU's mission and values and to demonstrate an active contribution to them.

ACU does not accept candidate applications submitted by external recruitment agencies through the ACU careers website.

Ad Text:
At ASIC, you can be the change that ensures a fair, strong and efficient financial system for the benefit of all Australians. Contribute to delivering on ASIC's purpose, vision, and strategic priorities to help maintain the integrity of the financial system and protect consumers from harm.

 

The Australian Government has announced the stabilisation of existing business registers and their transfer from the Australian Taxation Office (ATO) back to ASIC, under the Registry Connect (RC) Program. This program aims to deliver reliable, secure, trusted, and efficient registry services to support the economy for the benefit of all Australians.

 

36-Month Fixed Term Contract
Sydney or Melbourne location
Salary from $147,074 to $162,634 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications will close at 11:59pm AEDT, Thursday 2 October 2025

 

 

The team 

The Digital, Data & Technology (DD&T) Portfolio Office delivers a broad suite of services in portfolio management, project delivery, business planning, and governance to support ASIC's strategic priorities. We work in close partnership with ASIC IT and the newly established RegistryConnect (RC) program to ensure projects are aligned with both strategic direction and operational needs.

 

 

The role

The Senior Data Business Analyst will play a lead role in the delivery of actionable insights by transforming raw data into meaningful information using tools like Power BI. Operating within ASIC's RegistryConnect Program, the role supports strategic decision-making, drives stakeholder engagement, and ensures alignment between business needs and technical solutions.

More specifically, you will:

Lead Data Business Analysis practices at ASIC by applying established frameworks and supporting team delivery of project outcomes.
Champion the Data Business Analysis function and contribute to project success by aligning efforts with business objectives.
Collaborate with ASIC Registry Business, IT stakeholders, and the CDAO to elicit and document business data requirements.
Identify opportunities to enhance Data BA processes and promote innovation through effective stakeholder engagement.
Communicate business requirements clearly to data professionals, including Data Modellers, Architects, and Engineers.
Define and document data governance requirements, providing support throughout the project lifecycle, including Privacy Impact Assessments (PIAs).

 

 

About you

The ideal candidate for this role is a strategic and experienced data professional with significant experience in leading the delivery of actionable insights to support business decision-making. They will bring with them deep expertise in areas such as Data Business Analysis, championing innovation and ensure alignment between data initiatives and organisational goals.

 

As a confident communicator and trusted advisor, they will also demonstrate a proven ability to foster collaboration across business and technical teams to drive meaningful outcomes.

In addition, you will have:

Bachelor's degree or higher in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related discipline.
Strong ability to analyse business challenges, identify opportunities, and document clear, actionable requirements.
Proficient in developing user stories and acceptance criteria within DevOps environments.
Proven experience building and maintaining effective stakeholder relationships to drive outcomes.
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to translate technical concepts for non-technical audiences.
Extensive experience in data analysis and profiling using structured query languages (SQL).
Deep expertise in Databricks and Data Lake technologies.
Solid understanding of data modelling principles, including Data Vault 2.0 methodology.
Experienced in collaborating with Data Governance teams and understanding their compliance obligations.
Significant knowledge of data management principles and the full data lifecycle.

 

View the position description for more information or click ‘apply' to start your application.

Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Thursday 2 October 2025.

 

 

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

 

ASIC is committed to providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development

 

Click here to view ASIC's salary and benefits guide.

To read more about ASIC, you can visit our website or review our Corporate Plan.

To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.

Melbourne is Australia's fastest growing city, and public transport is vital to keeping it moving. Since 2009, Metro has proudly operated and maintained a world-class train service and delivered major transport projects that shape the future of our city. Guided by our value of Safely Always, we are one team dedicated to ensuring everyone gets home safely while helping to connect and create a better Melbourne.





The Senior Commercial Analyst will support the Infrastructure Services Group (ISG) in managing its multimillion-dollar budget, helping to deliver essential services that keep Melbourne's rail network running and support the city's Big Build. This includes financial and resource forecasting across key areas such as signalling, electrical works, vehicle and equipment management, safe network access, and operational training.

You'll work closely with project teams, finance, and workforce planning to deliver insights that enable smart decision-making and long-term planning. This is a permanent role based in Docklands, with a hybrid arrangement of 3 days in the office and 2 days working from home.

Key Responsibilities

Analyse and forecast budgets, track project finances, support workforce planning, and provide actionable insights.
Gather and document requirements, map processes, identify improvements, and support business case development.
Collaborate with ISG, finance, HR, and project teams to align forecasting with operational needs and build strong relationships.
Design and improve reporting tools, develop financial models and templates, and maintain key project documentation.
Assist in delivering process changes, run workshops, and support testing and communication for new tools or systems.
Enhance analytical tools, share expertise, and support capability building within the ISG team.


About you

Tertiary qualification in Business, Finance, Economics or equivalent experience as a Business Analyst.
Proven ability to interpret complex financial and resourcing data for analysis and forecasting.
Advanced proficiency in Excel, financial modelling, and Microsoft Office tools.
Strong ability to engage stakeholders and communicate complex information clearly.
Experience documenting business processes, gathering requirements, and producing quality reports and recommendations.
Background in project-based or infrastructure delivery settings, with the ability to manage competing priorities independently.

Click apply to submit your application by 11.59pm, Thursday 9 October 2025

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members. We are dedicated to building a high-performance environment underpinned by a strong risk culture, ensuring we deliver the best outcomes for our members.



Your New Role

We have a 12-month max-term contract opportunity for an experienced Investment Data Enablement Analyst to join the Data Enablement team. This role will support the implementation of solutions related to data acquisition, data mastering and data quality on various data/Investment management platforms, ensuring accurate and timely delivery of data to the investment department and the analytical insight team, as well as operationalising data governance policies and guidelines.

Key responsibilities will include;


Engage with stakeholders to design and develop investment data products.
Collaborate with Business Analysts and other stakeholders to ensure the completeness and accuracy of functional and non-functional requirements, data models, source-to-target mappings, and data quality control definitions.
Design data platform components to meet business requirements, encompassing Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) pipelines, metadata management, and data quality functionalities.
Develop and configure data platform components in alignment with business needs, including supporting metadata management within the enterprise data catalogue.
Package components and prepare release documentation, including extending and maintaining deployment pipelines.
Provide ongoing support for data platform operations including design documentation, BAU issue triage and resolution, and other business readiness activities, including ETL processes and data quality functionalities.

What You'll Need

Solid experience in investment management or within an asset owner organisation with demonstrated investment data management capability.
Comprehensive experience across multiple asset classes, with a strong understanding of market participants and the asset management business model.
Proficiency in defining functional and non-functional requirements, with prior exposure to product management practices.
Familiarity with upstream data sources commonly used by asset managers (e.g., custodians, portfolio management systems, data service providers).
Strong understanding of data modelling principles and patterns, as well as data platform architecture and design frameworks.
Experience with data management standards such as DCAM and DAMA.
Hands-on experience with the agile development lifecycle, including the design and implementation of ETL components within a data platform.
Ability to collaborate with development teams to review and enhance code quality, and to present technical solutions effectively to stakeholders.
Proficiency in data profiling and testing, including the use of test data and execution of unit, integration, acceptance, and performance testing for data platforms.
Knowledge of CI/CD pipelines and DevOps practices for data platform deployment and maintenance.
Strong debugging skills for data platforms and custom Python code, with experience in data observability and monitoring solutions.

Company Description


Lendi Group is a market-leading digital platform business that is focused on revolutionising the entire property journey. It operates Lendi - Australia’s original and #1 digital mortgage brand - and the iconic Aussie franchise.

Powered by an advanced AI proprietary platform, a national network of 1,300 brokers, 230 retail stores, a team of experienced buyer’s agents, integrated property search and conveyancing, Aussie is supporting customers at every step of their property journey to find, buy and own with more confidence than ever before. Lendi Group’s loan book is more than $100b and it was named Australia’s Aggregator of the Year for 2024.

To learn more about life at Lendi Group check out our blog: https://www.lendi.com.au/inspire/category/life-at-lendi/

Why Join Us?

Innovation at Our Core – We challenge the status quo and push boundaries to create better solutions.
Work with the Best – Collaborate with some of the brightest minds in fintech, financial services, and strategy.
Make an Impact – Contribute to meaningful projects that shape our business and the future of property finance.
Grow & Evolve – Develop your skills and advance your career in a fast-moving, purpose-driven environment.

To ensure we remain at the cutting edge of technological advancements, we are seeking a visionary and results-driven Data Science and Analytics Lead to join our Data Supergroup.

This role is pivotal in shaping the AI/ML strategy of the Group and deploying value-accretive solutions across the business. This senior position involves managing a team of around 10, including data scientists & analytics and partnering closely with senior business stakeholders across the Group including Growth, Customer, Origination and Technology.

You will have end-to-end accountability for the AI/ ML data product lifecycle from requirements gathering and ideation, to ongoing model maintenance and innovative product roadmap platform across the enterprise. 

Job Description


Strategic Leadership:

​​​​​​​Utilise strong commercial acumen to effectively translate the objectives and pain points of business stakeholders into technical requirements.
Operate as a strategic advisor to the business on value-drivers and return on investment for AI/ ML initiatives including identification of opportunities, prioritisation and end-to-end implementation)
Develop and implement the strategic roadmap for AI/ML initiatives across Lendi Group, and manage a portfolio of initiatives, in alignment with strategic business priorities and OKRs
Develop assessment frameworks for AI/ ML model deployment including measurable return on investment across business and customer interactions
Executive and Board engagement as required, including preparation of Board papers, business case and investment case papers

Innovation and Solution Deployment: 

Commercial assessment of initiatives and budget management, including use-case assessment and prioritisation, implementation of prioritisation frameworks and governance forums
Lead the design, development, and deployment of cutting-edge AI/ML solutions
Conduct vendor assessments to evaluate and recommend solutions, supporting the buy/ build/ acquire decision-making process
Ensure best practices in MLOps, model deployment and lifecycle management are followed to maintain high standards of performance, scalability, robustness and reliability
Ensure appropriate management of data science initiative costs, including vendors
Develop comprehensive solution design and implementation plans for AI/ ML solutions across the data science lifecycle and project stages including ongoing maintenance and monitoring
Work with cross-functional teams to operationalise AI/ ML in business operations and processes

Collaboration and Influence: 

Work closely with Growth, Customer, and Distribution teams to identify key business questions and use-cases that could be appropriately solved with AI/ ML solutions and determine the best solution
Collaborate with other data, technology and product teams to integrate AI solutions seamlessly into existing systems and workflows

Research and Development:

Stay current with the latest advancements in AI/ ML technologies and methodologies, integrating relevant innovations into the Lendi Group AI strategy and roadmap
Drive innovation by exploring and implementing new AI/ ML techniques and tools to solve complex business problems.
Deep engagement with end-users to understand requirements and take a product-led approach to problem solving and solution design

Mentorship and Team Development:

Mentor and provide technical guidance to data scientists and analysts fostering a culture of innovation and excellence. 
Foster a culture of continuous learning and creative problem solving within the data science team.
Implement best-practice documentation and data science lifecycle management practices.

Stakeholder Engagement:

Communicate complex concepts and solutions effectively to non-technical stakeholders.
Present AI/ML strategies and updates to senior management and other key stakeholders.
Be able to effectively communicate the value of AI/ ML solutions to business users and brokers

Qualifications


Degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Machine Learning, Statistics or a related field. Advanced degree preferred.
Experience in leading teams and managing initiatives across different business domains including working across data engineering, data analytics and data science
Extensive knowledge of the AI/ ML lifecycle including data collection, model development, deployment and monitoring
Demonstrated experience with MLOps and best practices in AI/ ML model management
Strong background in customer and marketing related AI/ ML use cases such as customer lifecycle management and content personalisation
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R and SQL and experience with Cloud platforms (AWS, Azure)
Familiarity with AI/ ML frameworks and tools e.g. PyTorch, Tensorflow
Excellent problem solving skills, a strategic mindset and the ability to think critically and creatively 
Passionate about the opportunity to push the envelope while protecting our customers data
Strong communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to influence and collaborate with stakeholders at all levels
Strong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to influence and engage stakeholders at all levels

Additional Information

Job Title: EY-P Manager or Senior Manager - Decision Modelling
Ad Text:
Company description:



At EY, we're all in to shape your future with confidence. We'll help you succeed in a globally connected powerhouse of diverse teams and take your career wherever you want it to go. Join EY and help to build a better working world.



Job description:



At EY-Parthenon, our unique combination of transformative strategy, transactions, tax and corporate finance delivers real-world value - solutions that work in practice, not just on paper. Benefiting from EY's full spectrum of services, we've reimagined strategic consulting to work in a world of increasing complexity. With deep functional and sector expertise, paired with innovative AI-powered technology and an investor mindset, we partner with CEOs, boards, private equity and governments every step of the way.

The opportunity

We're looking for a Manager or Senior Manager to join our Decision Modelling team in Melbourne during a time of strong growth. As part of our national valuations and decision support modelling team, you'll manage, deliver and review a wide range of modelling engagements supporting our clients in making critical business decisions. You will also have the opportunity to grow our market presence and lead in the winning of work. Working with a wide variety of clients and industries, you'll gain experience in understanding client issues and building client relationships. In our friendly, collaborative environment, you'll receive the support, formal training and coaching you need to further progress your career.

This is a hybrid position based in Naarm - Melbourne.

Your key responsibilities

Lead financial modelling projects for various purposes such as management planning, mergers and acquisitions, financial reporting, tax and regulatory compliance, restructuring and reorganisation, and corporate strategy.
Identify issues and propose strategies related to the procedures executed
Assume a leadership role in report generation and detailed financial modelling
Build and nurture positive, productive, and professional relationships with both internal and external clients.
Collaborate effectively with team members, mentor colleagues, stay informed about current business and economic trends relevant to clients, and leverage the latest technology and tools to enhance service delivery.
Seek out and seize new business opportunities, participating in client proposals and presentations to grow the modelling practice. This includes identifying client needs and tailoring solutions to meet strategic goals.
Mentor and develop junior team members through delegation and hands-on training, fostering an inclusive and innovative team environment.

Skills and attributes for success

A bachelor's degree with around 8 years of relevant work experience, or a master's degree with approximately 7 years of related work experience.
Exceptional numerical and analytical skills, preferably with a degree in Accounting & Finance, Commerce or Economics.
Strong experience in building and managing complex financial model builds and reviews. This includes expertise in 3-way financial models, project finance, and scenario modelling. Ability to help our clients solve complex problems by providing key insights. You should be able to demonstrate storytelling capabilities, ensuring outputs are clearly connected and insights are presented in a compelling manner. Additionally, models should be robust and flexible in design.
Experience in Energy, project finance and / or infrastructure or cost modelling would be highly valued.
Experience in team leadership, business development and client management.
Ability to manage project expenditures against budget and revenue, and provide guidance to team members to ensure the completion of work deliverables.

Candidates with experience in leading and developing high quality teams will be highly valued with technical expertise in MS Excel including VBA and Power Query being essential. Experience or awareness with other analytics tools and technologies, will also be valued.

What we look for

At EY, we'll fuel you and your extraordinary talents in a diverse and inclusive culture of globally connected teams. Learn more.

A comprehensive benefits package: From a yearly wellness incentive, to access to additional 8 weeks of flex leave per year, and family-friendly policies, including 26 weeks of gender-neutral paid parental leave, we cater to your diverse needs to help you thrive both personally and professionally www.ey.com/au/benefits

About the Role

The Senior ML Engineer is a key role within Data Platforms, responsible for delivering innovative and sustainable data driven solutions contributing to Sportsbet having a competitive advantage in the Machine Learning domain within the quant space.

This is an exciting opportunity support our industry leading Data Science team, delivering cutting edge customer facing models into production and optimising their performance, along with contributing key capabilities back into our international Flutter brands for wider use. Your day could see you doing:

Build feature pipelines, model inference services, and monitoring tools.
Design and implement CI/CD pipelines with automated testing.
Standardise ML delivery patterns and best practices across teams.
Lead delivery estimation and ensure accountability for outcomes.
Identify and close gaps across DevOps, security, and operations.
Optimise ML systems for performance, reliability, and cost.
Own what you build — monitor, troubleshoot, and resolve production issues.
Drive automation and continuous improvement across ML workflows.
Share expertise and promote innovation.

About You

You have the ability to ask the right questions with an eye for detail with an interest in building price assurance framework tools. We would like you to have:

Proficiency in developing software models in Rust / Python / C family, leveraging sub-model architectures to build modularised application in a solver / simulation-based application.
Strong expertise in designing low-latency application backed with demonstrable knowledge of concurrency, parallelisation, performance tuning, while enforcing memory safety
Strong experience leading the SDLC for Machine Learning and Data Science models, building ML pipelines, feature stores and containerisation utilising Docker / Kubernetes
Proven experience in designing, training, and validating machine learning models for real-time prediction tasks (e.g., regression, classification, time-series, anomaly detection).
Well-versed in model experimentation and evaluation techniques (e.g., A/B testing, back-testing, cross-validation, error analysis).
Familiarity with data models such as Data Vault, Kimball, and Medallion architecture (ideal but not essential)

Why You’ll Love Working Here

Along with a competitive salary and generous performance-based bonus, here’s some of our other benefits:

25 days annual leave (plus flexible working options)
$1050 work-from-home allowance
Access to outstanding career development programs, including expert-led internal training and external learning opportunities
Onsite concierge services, free meals, social events and access to the Sportsbet Salon
Generous parental leave and return-to-work benefits
Hack Days: Participate in our hack days, where creativity and collaboration lead to exciting new ideas and projects.

Ad Text:
Impactful work on key projects relating to critical national payments infrastructure

Develop your career in a collaborative environment

Contract until Nov 2026, in a hybrid working environment


Do work that makes a difference

The Reserve Bank of Australia is undertaking a Core Modernisation program which involves a major upgrade of core technology infrastructure. We have a great opportunity for multiple senior business analysts to join the team and make a key contribution to the business analysis activities of the Payments Migration workstream.

This workstream centres on critical payments systems for Australia including the Reserve Bank Information and Transfer System (RITS), the Fast Settlement Service (FSS) and Swift systems used for interbank payments. Safe, secure and reliable settlement systems are integral to the smooth functioning of the Australian economy, and projects relating to these systems are an important aspect of the RBA's work.


About the role

The type of work you will do will include:

Translating complex business, strategic, and technical information for diverse audiences

Collaborating with stakeholders to capture and document requirements

Creating and maintaining Jira user stories, acceptance criteria, and backlog refinement

Acting as a liaison between business units, IT, and infrastructure teams to align solutions with business goals

Ensuring compliance with regulatory, security, and technology assurance frameworks

Applying a strong understanding of on-prem infrastructure, virtual machines, networking, and enterprise IT environments

Leading end-to-end business analysis activities across multiple workstreams

Facilitating workshops and stakeholder engagement sessions to drive consensus and clarity

Supporting solution design and architecture discussions with technical teams

Managing traceability of requirements through to testing and implementation


About you

You'll bring:

Proven experience in integration projects, application projects, application migration with expertise in data centre migrations

Strong stakeholder management and proven communication skills across business and technical domains

Advanced proficiency in business analysis tools, methods, and communication techniques

Proficiency in Jira and Confluence for managing requirements, workflows, and documentation

Skill in creating clear and impactful presentations for workshops, training, and senior management

Experience in Agile and hybrid delivery environments, including sprint planning and backlog grooming

A quick learning ability and adaptability to complex, unfamiliar environments

Strong experience in Requirements Management, with the ability to independently manage BA activities and deliverables

Hands-on experience with solution evaluation, analysis, documentation, and recommendations

The ability to communicate complex technical issues to both business and technical audiences

Leadership and mentoring experience within the BA community to support the growth of BA practices

A strategic mindset with the ability to connect business needs to technology outcomes


Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people.

Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve.

We encourage intelligent inquiry, and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Senior Data Engineer

$200k – $230k package · Sydney or Remote (Australia)

About the Company

Join a fast-growing technology business that builds modern data and analytics platforms to power customer and market insights.
They value trust, collaboration and autonomy, with a culture that rewards impact and supports life outside of work.

About the Role

As Senior Data Engineer, you’ll design and operate the core data environment that ingests, organises and serves high-volume customer and market data.
This is a hands-on position blending data engineering and data infrastructure, focusing on R, Python and SQL and working across on-premises and cloud environments.

What You’ll Do

Design and build scalable, high-performance data pipelines to ingest and process large, complex datasets from multiple internal and external sources.

Model and manage data flows and schemas to ensure quality, consistency and reliability.

Implement best practices in data governance, access control, monitoring and observability.

Work with product and analytics teams to align data architecture with business goals.

Automate infrastructure provisioning and deployments using modern DevOps and Infrastructure-as-Code tools.

Provide production support, including continuous improvement of system performance, availability and disaster recovery.

What You Bring

Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or equivalent experience.

Proficiency in R, Python and SQL with strong data modelling and query optimisation skills.

Solid understanding of distributed systems, modern data storage (e.g. S3, columnar stores) and streaming technologies (e.g. Kafka).

Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP) and Linux.

Familiarity with orchestration tools (Airflow, Dagster) and container technologies (Docker, Kubernetes).

Strong communication skills and the ability to work effectively in small, fast-moving teams as well as larger enterprise environments.

Nice to Have

Experience working end-to-end in small, agile environments, taking full ownership of design and delivery.

Exposure to modern data formats (Delta Lake, Apache Iceberg) and data lakehouse architectures.

Experience with observability tools (Prometheus, Grafana).

Why Join

Play a key role in shaping a greenfield data platform used for advanced analytics and data-driven decision making.

Work with modern tooling across both cloud and on-prem environments.

Join a supportive, collaborative culture with flexibility for remote work.

About the Organisation

Carinity believe that true care begins with seeing the person - not just their needs, but their story, strengths, and their hopes. Whether it's providing aged care, walking alongside young people, supporting families, or offering spiritual comfort, the care provided by Carinity is deeply personal. Understanding is the foundation of everything they do - because meaningful care requires a genuine connection.

Their care has a lasting impact. It’s felt in the confidence of a student finding their path, the peace of an older person feeling safe and valued, and the strength of a family supported through life’s challenges. Founded in faith 75 years ago, and driven by purpose, Carinity exists to make a difference – one person, one moment, one lasting impact at a time.

About the Position

This is an exciting opportunity to join Carinity in a newly created leadership role within Carinity’s Aged Care division. As the Business Insights & Analytics Manager, you will be at the forefront of driving innovation and improvement across their residential and community aged care services. Reporting directly to the Executive Manager Aged Care, you will use actionable insights to tell the story behind the operations - helping the organisation optimise resources, strengthen financial outcomes, and deliver sustainable, high-quality care.

You will collaborate closely with teams across Finance, Operations, ICT, and HR to influence decisions at the highest levels and ensure the business remains agile in a changing aged care landscape. This role is not to be mistaken for a traditional reporting role. It is to uncover meaningful insights from the data and guide the business in turning those insights into practical, measurable actions. By leading cross-functional initiatives and embedding a culture of data-informed decision-making, your influence will extend across the Aged Care division.

Based at Carinity’s Gaythorne corporate office, with occasional travel throughout Queensland, this position offers a unique opportunity to combine strategic leadership with purpose-driven impact.

About the Person

We are seeking a visionary leader with strong commercial acumen and a passion for using data to make a difference. You will bring tertiary qualifications in Business, Analytics, Health Services, or a related discipline, along with significant experience in analytics, business performance, or financial modelling, ideally from complex, regulated, and customer centric environments. You will be highly proficient in tools such as Power BI and Excel and experienced in working with HRIS and workforce data.

As a natural collaborator, you will thrive on building relationships across teams, simplifying complex information into actionable insights, and influencing decision-making at senior levels. You will be solutions-focused, strategic, confident and above all, you will share a commitment to values-based care and have the drive to create meaningful change for older Australians.

To submit your application, please click Apply Now and include your resume and cover letter by Friday 10th October 2025.

Blackmores has embarked on strategic business transformation as we introduce new ways working across our ERP and tech. landscape. This transformation period will enable efficiencies and a reimagined employee experience as we deliver a new, enterprise-wide ERP (SAP) and optimise our Supply Chain.

Reporting into the Data & Analytics Workstream Lead, this role is responsible to guide the design, development, and delivery of enterprise-wide reporting and data analytics capabilities on our SAP transformation. The ideal candidate will have a credible background in enterprise reporting, data modelling, and analytics strategy. You will also demonstrate a deep understanding of SAP data structures and BI tools. 

This is a fantastic opportunity to join our greenfield SAP implementation on a multi-year secondment.

What we offer?

Opportunities to support your local community through paid community leave

WGEA certified work environment

Flexible working across most of our roles

A socially responsible work environment, on track to be carbon neutral by 2030

Great benefits to support your health and wellbeing, including access to discounted products

Mental health support for you and your family through our Sonder assistance program

Responsibilities include:

Define and lead the end-to-end reporting and analytics strategy aligned with program goals, business requirements, and SAP best practices. 
Identify opportunities to leverage standard SAP reports and analytics content to reduce custom development and accelerate delivery. 
Evaluate, recommend, and implement reporting optimizations to improve performance, usability, and maintainability. 
Oversee the design, development, and deployment of reporting and analytics solutions across SAP modules in scope. 
Collaborate with business stakeholders to define KPIs, reporting needs, and data visualization requirements, ensuring alignment with strategic objectives.

Who are you?

10+ years of experience in Reporting and Analytics, with a strong focus on ERP environments, including SAP S/4HANA

Expertise in SAP Analytics Cloud (SAC) for dashboard development, predictive analytics, and planning scenarios, including integration with S/4HANA, and non-SAP systems. 

Extensive hands-on experience with Power BI – data modeling, DAX, custom visuals, and enterprise report development – with seamless integration into SAP and other enterprise data sources. 

Demonstrated history of working on end-to-end SAP implementations

Strong stakeholder management capabilities, including cross-functional collaboration with business users, IT, and third-party vendors. 

Excellent communication skills with experience in executive reporting, storytelling with data, and driving adoption of self-service analytics.

Salary: Competitive salary package + range of benefits

Job description:


Own high-impact initiatives across SAP SuccessFactors
Work across multiple modules and integrations
Drive real outcomes in a challenging, growth-focused environment

The opportunity to join our team

We're looking for a Senior SuccessFactors Analyst to take ownership of high-impact initiatives and shape how HR technology supports a wide reaching workforce. This is a hands-on, strategic role where you'll lead complex projects, manage critical integrations, and influence the delivery of HR solutions in a fast-paced, highly regulated financial services environment.

You'll work across almost every SuccessFactors module, including Employee Central, Performance, Compensation, Learning, Recruiting, and Onboarding, while navigating integrations with HR, Finance, IAM, and Payroll systems. This is far from a narrow support role - you'll balance business-as-usual improvements with high-stakes, cross-functional projects, ensuring systems are optimised, compliant, and effective.

If you're looking for a role that offers challenge, visibility, and the opportunity to make a tangible impact, this is a chance to grow your expertise and advance your career.

What You'll Be Doing:

Lead the configuration, optimization, and enhancement of multiple SAP SuccessFactors modules, with a strong focus on Employee Central
Manage complex integrations and act as the escalation point for critical issues, ensuring compliance with finance industry regulations
Collaborate with People & Culture, Risk & Compliance, Enterprise Technology, and external consulting partners to deliver innovative HR solutions
Support BAU activities, streamline workflows, and contribute to upgrades and testing cycles

What you will bring

Proven hands-on SAP SuccessFactors experience across multiple modules, with strong configuration, integration, and troubleshooting skills
Deep understanding of HR processes, compliance, and regulations in a financial services environment
Leadership skills to guide initiatives, manage projects, and influence stakeholders without direct reports
Experience with Employee Central Payroll (ECP) is a plus
Familiarity with JIRA, ServiceNow, SharePoint, Confluence, and SAP ALM
SAP SuccessFactors certifications preferred

Find the better way

What gets us excited about working here? Helping people feel good about their money as one of Australia's leading financial wellbeing organisations. From those starting out to those retiring. As your team, we'll show up for you and together we will create financial wellbeing for every Australian. Because we know people who are confident about their financial future live better lives.

If this sounds like your kind of career, you sound like our kind of person. With us, you'll do work that builds your technical know-how and challenges our entire industry to move forward. Along the way, you'll be free to explore new ideas and technology, solve problems in a team, and independently to get great things done. Around here, we like to call it "putting our fingerprints on the future".

People-inspired tech

Deep expertise combined with creativity can take on the trickiest of problems. Join our team of brilliant minds and mentors as we explore our way to innovation and apply technology in more human ways than ever.

To Apply

Read more here about why you should join our team.

About UniSuper
UniSuper is a leader in the superannuation industry, known for delivering strong performance and exceptional retirement outcomes for our members. As we continue to grow, we offer meaningful opportunities for talented professionals to develop their careers and contribute to our success. Join our collaborative and forward-thinking team, where your expertise and ideas will help shape the future of retirement for Australians.

Over 70% of all funds under management (FUM) are managed in-house by our dedicated Investments team. We strongly believe our in-house management strategy ultimately leads to greater retirement outcomes for our members through lower fees, sustainable investment options and top quartile investment performance.

The Opportunity
We are seeking a Senior Investment Analyst, with a focus on the Financials sector to join our Equities team. This role is pivotal in supporting the management and execution of UniSuper’s equities investment strategy, contributing to the delivery of strong, sustainable returns for our members.

As a Senior Investment Analyst, you will:

Drive and support the origination, analysis, and execution of equity investments, including due diligence, financial modelling, and valuation analysis.  A primary area of sector focus is intended to be in Financials including Banks and Insurance.
Lead and coordinate transaction processes for acquisitions and divestments within the equities portfolio.
Actively manage and monitor portfolio performance, including stakeholder and regulatory reporting, and support the valuation process for listed and unlisted equities.
Prepare and present investment recommendations and reports to UniSuper’s Investment Committee and other key stakeholders.
Represent UniSuper on portfolio company boards and at industry forums as required.
Proactively generate, develop, and present investment ideas and research in the equities sector.
Collaborate closely with other asset class teams within the broader investments group.
Incorporate AI and innovative technologies into investment processes to enhance efficiency and decision-making.

About You
You are a driven investment professional with a passion for delivering outstanding results in equities. Your analytical mindset, commercial acumen, and collaborative approach set you apart, and you thrive in environments where you can make a tangible impact on portfolio performance and team success.

To excel in this role, you will bring:

7–10+ years’ experience in equities investing, funds management, investment banking, or professional services (with a focus on M&A advisory, financial due diligence, and/or valuations).  Specific experience in Financials including Banks and Insurance would be prioritised.  
Advanced financial modelling, analytical, and quantitative skills, with the ability to synthesise results and provide actionable commercial insights.
Excellent presentation, verbal, and written communication skills, enabling you to engage and build relationships with a broad range of stakeholders.
Demonstrated self-motivation, attention to detail, and the ability to work proactively, meet deadlines, and function effectively both in a team and autonomously.
Relevant tertiary and professional qualifications (such as CA or CFA), with a commitment to ongoing professional development.
A passion for superannuation and delivering positive retirement outcomes for members, with experience or interest in integrating technology and AI into investment processes.

Why UniSuper?
This position is based in Melbourne, with some domestic and international travel required. We take a long-term outlook and invest in our employees’ development, offering a personal development plan and yearly funding to support your career goals. We believe 60% in-office is the best way to collaborate and build relationships, while still offering flexibility.

If you feel you have the experience and skills required for this role, please apply!
